======================================================================
Part 2: dim(Omega_p) vs sum_{|S|=p+1} H(T[S])
If Omega_p = C(n,p+1), all subsets have H=1 (transitive-like)
Surplus = dim(Omega_p) - C(n,p+1)
Total H = sum_{|S|=p+1} H(T[S])
Excess H = Total H - C(n,p+1) = sum of (H(T[S])-1)
======================================================================

  n=5, p=2: correlation(surplus, excess_H) = -0.2358
    surplus range: [-2, 0]
    excess_H range: [0, 10]
    (excess_H -> surplus) mapping:
      excess_H=0: surplus=0 (deterministic)
      excess_H=2: surplus=-1 (deterministic)
      excess_H=4: surplus=-1 (deterministic)
      excess_H=6: surplus=-1 (deterministic)
      excess_H=8: surplus in [np.int64(-2), np.int64(-1), np.int64(0)] (55 samples)
      excess_H=10: surplus=0 (deterministic)

  n=5, p=3: correlation(surplus, excess_H) = 0.2533
